label("$Q$",(0,1,0),E);
label("$A$",(0,1,1/4),E);
draw((1/2,1/2,1/4)--(0,1,1/4));
[/asy]

Since $\overline{PA}$ is half a diagonal of the top face, we have $PA = 16\sqrt{2}$ cm.  From right triangle $PAQ$, we have $PQ = \sqrt{PA^2 + AQ^2} = \sqrt{512+64} = \boxed{24}$ cm.

First, it is probably a good idea to sketch our triangle: [asy]
pair A, B, C, M, N, P;
A = (0, 6);
B = (0, 0);
C = (5.196, 0);
M = 0.5 * B + 0.5 * C;
N = 0.5 * A + 0.5 * B;
P = 0.66 * N + 0.34 * C;
draw(A--B--C--cycle);
