label("Z",(-5,-12),S);
label("Y",(12,5),E);

[/asy]

We know that $TX=TZ$, since both are radii of length 6.  We are given $\angle TXZ=60^{\circ}$, so $\angle TZX=60^{\circ}$, and triangle $TXZ$ is equilateral.  Thus, $TX=TZ=XZ=\boxed{6}$.

